  <original-body>When running ActiveRecord without the entire Rails stack, ActiveRecord::Base.logger isn't automatically set. So when migrations are run this line fails

@@@ ruby
   Base.logger.info &quot;Migrating to #{migration.name} (#{migration.version})&quot;
@@@

Placing an **if Base.logger** at the end seems to be the simplest switch.</original-body>
